# Golden ratio sizing

When choosing font sizes, spacing, or proportional layout values, use the project's φ-based scale — do not pick arbitrary Tailwind defaults or one-off pixel values.

## Typography

Use semantic classes from `src/index.css`:

- `type-h1` … `type-h5`, `type-h2-sm`, `type-eyebrow`
- `type-body`, `type-body-lg`, `type-body-sm`, `type-caption`
- `type-display`, `type-display-lg`

Underlying tokens: `text-phi-xs` through `text-phi-5xl` in `tailwind.config.js` (base 16px, ratio φ ≈ 1.618).

## Spacing

Prefer `phi-*` spacing tokens (`phi-1` … `phi-6`) when adding padding, gaps, or margins that should relate to the type scale.

## Fonts

- Headings (h1–h5): Queens Compressed Trial (`font-serif` / `type-h*`)
- Body: Funnel Sans (`font-sans` / `type-body*`)
- Eyebrows: Funnel Sans (`type-eyebrow`)

## Buttons

- Non-hero: `btn-primary` (dark background, white text, `rounded-[2px]`)
- Hero / dark sections: `btn-hero-cta` or `btn-primary` on `bg-heading` (auto-inverts to white)
